The paper proposes a method for generating high-resolution photo-realistic images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The method uses generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a popular topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of text descriptions as inputs, which could fall under the natural language processing (cs.CL) category, but since the focus is on image synthesis, it is less likely. Finally, the paper involves generating images at multiple scales, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM) categories.
